Bring a #medium pot{} of @water{for boiling} with @salt{for water} to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lime{1}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{10%oz} and press into an even layer using a #spatula{}. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{2-3%minutes}.

While pork cooks, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together @umi ginger sauce{2%oz}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz}, @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp}, and juice from half the lime.

Add scallion whites and @garlic powder{1%tsp} to pan with pork. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @shelled edamame{4%oz}, @soy sauce{2%tbsp}, and @ponzu sauce{12%ml}; cook until liquid has absorbed and pork is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in ¼ of the chili-ginger sauce. Remove from heat; cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, once water is boiling, add ¾ of the @ramen noodles{6%oz} to pot (save the rest for another use). Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Drain and rinse thoroughly under cold water, ~{30%seconds}.

Add drained noodles to pan with pork mixture. Pour remaining chili-ginger sauce over noodles; toss until thoroughly coated and combined.

Divide noodles between #bowls{}. Top with scallion greens and @peanuts{1/2%oz}. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> This all-in-one meal is ready in about 15 minutes!